[Social distancing, masks, and school closures have had "benefits" not only in preventing spread of SARS-CoV-2, but also other air-borne viruses such as influenza (see next post) and measles. - Mod.LK]

******
[2] UK: Flu, measles, mumps & rubella infections plummet
Date: Sat 27 Feb 2021
Source: CGTN [abridged, edited]
https://newseu.cgtn.com/news/2021-02-27/Flu-measles-mumps-and-rubella-infection-numbers-plummet-in-UK-YcUGRkx6cE/index.html


Outbreaks of flu, measles, mumps, and rubella have been almost non-existent in the UK since the outbreak of COVID-19, a batch of scientific data has confirmed.

Out of 685 243 samples tested by Public Health England, not a single case of influenza was detected in the 1st 7 weeks of 2021.

The imposition of social distancing, combined with the prevalence of face coverings and handwashing, have been credited with blocking the usual routes of transmission for influenza. The reduction in international travel and an increased uptake in the flu vaccine probably also had a major impact.

[Byline: Jim Drury]

