Communicated by:
ProMED from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Qilla Abdullah or Abdullah Qilla is a district in the northwest of Balochistan province of Pakistan.

Also see:
Mere MO, Goodson JL, Chandio AK, et al. Progress Toward Measles Elimination -- Pakistan, 2000-2018. MMWR Morb Mortal Wkly Rep 2019;68:505-510. DOI: http://dx.doi.org/10.15585/mmwr.mm6822a4external icon:

"In the 2 decades before 2000, estimated coverage with the 1st measles-containing vaccine dose (MCV1) in Pakistan was 57% or less. The number of reported measles cases per year averaged approximately 29 000 during 1980-1989 and 3900 during 1990-1999.

What is added by this report?
Estimated MCV1 coverage increased from 57% to 76% during 2000-2017, and 2nd-dose coverage increased from 30% to 45% during 2009-2017. Approximately 232.5 million children were vaccinated with MCV during 2005-2018 vaccination campaigns. Despite these efforts, MCV coverage remained well below the recommended level of 95%, and measles incidence increased during 2010-2018.

What are the implications for public health practice?
To achieve measles elimination, efforts are needed to increase 2-dose vaccine coverage, reach communities not accessing immunization services, and increase measles surveillance sensitivity.

To advance progress toward measles elimination in Pakistan, there is a need to raise the visibility of measles elimination efforts, including the benefits of achieving measles elimination. Without jeopardizing the focused efforts to interrupt poliovirus transmission, transitioning the substantial polio infrastructure and resources should be carefully managed to support measles elimination and broader EMR vaccination goals."

This report was pre-COVID; consequently, the impact of COVID is not reflected in the numbers. If the measles vaccination campaign could piggyback on the polio immunization program, that would be highly efficient and effective. During COVID, the UAE-Pakistan Assistance Program campaign managed to reach out to some 16 million children and provided over 52 515 000 doses [of polio vaccine] since July 2020 (https://reliefweb.int/report/pakistan/uae-pap-administers-508-mn-doses-polio-vaccine-over-86-mn-children-pakistan-7-years). If measles vaccination could be given at the same time as polio, that would greatly facilitate measles control. - Mod.LK

